                <h3>Housing Prediction +<br>Convolutional Neural Networks</h3>
                <a href="https://github.com/palmaz9/AI_class" target="_blank">
                    <img class="project-img" src="/images/cnn.jpeg" alt="Housing Prediction Image">
                </a>
                <p>In my AI class, I worked on projects using TensorFlow and Keras. The first project involved building a deep learning model for predicting housing prices using the California Housing dataset. I utilized scikit-learn for data preprocessing and developed a neural network, improving the model with Adam optimizer and evaluating it using Mean Squared Error. The second project was an image classification model using a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) to classify images from the CIFAR-10 dataset. The model consisted on convolutional layers, batch normalization, and dropout for regularization. I improved its performance with data augmentation and learning rate scheduling.<br><b>Click on the image above to access the projects!</b></p>
