                <p>Because I became a chess enthusiast during my Information Technology Master's program, I build a guide on how to create a chess engine. This guide consists on simple required steps in order to build your own chess engine. It focused on creating the basic components of a chess engine, such as representing the chessboard, generating possible moves, and evaluating different positions on the board. I choose algorithms like Minimax with alpha-beta pruning to help the engine decide the best moves by simulating different scenarios and outcomes. Throughout this project, I gained a deeper understanding of how artificial intelligence can be applied to the chess world.<br><b> Click on the image above to download my paper. Have fun!</b></p>
